  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200°C/ 180°C (fan)/ gas 6</p><p>Boil half a kettle</p><p>Chop your <strong>waxy</strong> <strong>potatoes</strong> in half, lengthways</p><p>Add the<strong> chopped potatoes</strong> to a baking tray with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper </strong>and give everything a good mix up, then put the tray in the oven for 25-30 min or until golden</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-copy-3-1647965857402-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-copy-3-1647965857402-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-copy-3-1647965857402-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-copy-3-1647965857402-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-copy-3-1647965857402-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Peel and quarter your <strong>shallots</strong></p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>quartered shallots</strong> to the pan with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until they begin to caramelise and have slightly softened</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-copy-3-1647965877938-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-copy-3-1647965877938-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-copy-3-1647965877938-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-copy-3-1647965877938-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-copy-3-1647965877938-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the shallots are caramelising, peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Slice half your<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span><strong>asparagus </strong>lengthways, then chop the <strong>remaining asparagus</strong> into bite-sized pieces</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-copy-3-1647965887463-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-copy-3-1647965887463-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-copy-3-1647965887463-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-copy-3-1647965887463-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-copy-3-1647965887463-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the shallots have caramelised, add the <strong>chopped garlic</strong> to the pan with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 1 min further or until the garlic has softened</p><p>Once softened, add your <strong>creamy</strong> <strong>single soy</strong> to the pan with your <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong> and 50ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[65ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[80ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Season with a generous grind of <strong>black pepper </strong>and bring to the boil over a high heat, once boiling, reduce the heat to low and cook for 6-7 min or until reduced to a thicker consistency</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
